  52. (* determines if the string is an infix string.
  53.    checks backwards, first allowing a renaming postfix ("_102") which
  54.    may have resulted from Pexp -> Texp -> Pexp translation, then checking
  55.    if all the characters in the beginning of the string are valid infix

  57. ‌let fixity_of_string  = function
  58.   | "" -> `Normal
  59.   | s when List.mem s special_infix_strings -> `Infix s
  60.   | s when List.mem s.[0] infix_symbols -> `Infix s
  61.   | s when List.mem s.[0] prefix_symbols -> `Prefix s
  62.   | s when s.[0] = '.' -> `Mixfix s
  63.   | s when letop s -> `Letop s
  64.   | s when andop s -> `Andop s
  65.   | _ -> `Normal

  184. ‌let list : 'a . ?sep:space_formatter -> ?first:space_formatter ->
  185.   ?last:space_formatter -> (Format.formatter -> 'a -> unit) ->
  186.   Format.formatter -> 'a list -> unit
  187.   = fun ?sep ?first ?last fu f xs ->
  188.     let first = match first with Some x -> x |None -> ("": _ format6)
  189.     and last = match last with Some x -> x |None -> ("": _ format6)
  190.     and sep = match sep with Some x -> x |None -> ("@ ": _ format6) in
  191.     let aux f = function
  192.       | [] -> ()
  193.       | [x] -> fu f x
  194.       | xs ->
  195.           let rec loop  f = function
  196.             | [x] -> fu f x
  197.             | x::xs ->  fu f x; pp f sep; loop f xs;
  198.             | _ -> assert false in begin
  199.             pp f first; loop f xs; pp f last;
  200.           end in
  201.     aux f xs

  203. ‌let option : 'a. ?first:space_formatter -> ?last:space_formatter ->
  204.   (Format.formatter -> 'a -> unit) -> Format.formatter -> 'a option -> unit
  205.   = fun  ?first  ?last fu f a ->
  206.     let first = match first with Some x -> x | None -> ("": _ format6)
  207.     and last = match last with Some x -> x | None -> ("": _ format6) in
  208.     match a with
  209.     | None -> ()
  210.     | Some x -> pp f first; fu f x; pp f last

  212. ‌let paren: 'a . ?first:space_formatter -> ?last:space_formatter ->
  213.   bool -> (Format.formatter -> 'a -> unit) -> Format.formatter -> 'a -> unit
  214.   = fun  ?(first=("": _ format6)) ?(last=("": _ format6)) b fu f x ->
  215.     if b then (pp f "("; pp f first; fu f x; pp f last; pp f ")")
  216.     else fu f x

  288. and type_with_label ctxt f (label, c) =

  294. and core_type ctxt f x =
  295.   if x.ptyp_attributes <> [] then begin
  296.     pp f "((%a)%a)" (core_type ctxt) {x with ptyp_attributes=[]}
  297.       (attributes ctxt) x.ptyp_attributes
  298.   end
  299.   else match x.ptyp_desc with
  300.     | Ptyp_arrow (l, ct1, ct2) ->
  301.         pp f "@[<2>%a@;->@;%a@]" (* FIXME remove parens later *)
  302.           (type_with_label ctxt) (l,ct1) (core_type ctxt) ct2
  303.     | Ptyp_alias (ct, s) ->
  304.         pp f "@[<2>%a@;as@;%a@]" (core_type1 ctxt) ct tyvar s
  305.     | Ptyp_poly ([], ct) ->
  306.         core_type ctxt f ct
  307.     | Ptyp_poly (sl, ct) ->
  308.         pp f "@[<2>%a%a@]"
  309.                (fun f l -> match l with
  310.                   | [] -> ()
  311.                   | _ ->
  312.                       pp f "%a@;.@;"
  313.                         (list tyvar_loc ~sep:"@;")  l)
  314.           sl (core_type ctxt) ct
  315.     | _ -> pp f "@[<2>%a@]" (core_type1 ctxt) x

  317. and core_type1 ctxt f x =
  318.   if x.ptyp_attributes <> [] then core_type ctxt f x
  319.   else match x.ptyp_desc with
  320.     | Ptyp_any -> pp f "_";
  321.     | Ptyp_var s -> tyvar f  s;
  322.     | Ptyp_tuple l ->  pp f "(%a)" (list (core_type1 ctxt) ~sep:"@;*@;") l
  323.     | Ptyp_constr (li, l) ->
  324.         pp f (* "%a%a@;" *) "%a%a"
  325.           (fun f l -> match l with
  326.              |[] -> ()
  327.              |[x]-> pp f "%a@;" (core_type1 ctxt)  x
  328.              | _ -> list ~first:"(" ~last:")@;" (core_type ctxt) ~sep:",@;" f l)
  329.           l longident_loc li
  330.     | Ptyp_variant (l, closed, low) ->
  331.         let first_is_inherit = match l with
  332.           | {Parsetree.prf_desc = Rinherit _}::_ -> true
  333.           | _ -> false in
  334.         let type_variant_helper f x =
  335.           match x.prf_desc with
  336.           | Rtag (l, _, ctl) ->
  337.               pp f "@[<2>%a%a@;%a@]" (iter_loc string_quot) l
  338.                 (fun f l -> match l with
  339.                    |[] -> ()
  340.                    | _ -> pp f "@;of@;%a"
  341.                             (list (core_type ctxt) ~sep:"&")  ctl) ctl
  342.                 (attributes ctxt) x.prf_attributes
  343.           | Rinherit ct -> core_type ctxt f ct in
  344.         pp f "@[<2>[%a%a]@]"
  345.           (fun f l ->
  346.              match l, closed with
  347.              | [], Closed -> ()
  348.              | [], Open -> pp f ">" (* Cf #7200: print [>] correctly *)
  349.              | _ ->
  350.                  pp f "%s@;%a"
  351.                    (match (closed,low) with
  352.                     | (Closed,None) -> if first_is_inherit then " |" else ""
  353.                     | (Closed,Some _) -> "<" (* FIXME desugar the syntax sugar*)
  354.                     | (Open,_) -> ">")
  355.                    (list type_variant_helper ~sep:"@;<1 -2>| ") l) l
  356.           (fun f low -> match low with
  357.              |Some [] |None -> ()
  358.              |Some xs ->
  359.                  pp f ">@ %a"
  360.                    (list string_quot) xs) low
  361.     | Ptyp_object (l, o) ->
  362.         let core_field_type f x = match x.pof_desc with
  363.           | Otag (l, ct) ->
  364.             (* Cf #7200 *)
  365.             pp f "@[<hov2>%s: %a@ %a@ @]" l.txt
  366.               (core_type ctxt) ct (attributes ctxt) x.pof_attributes
  367.           | Oinherit ct ->
  368.             pp f "@[<hov2>%a@ @]" (core_type ctxt) ct
  369.         in
  370.         let field_var f = function
  371.           | Asttypes.Closed -> ()
  372.           | Asttypes.Open ->
  373.               match l with
  374.               | [] -> pp f ".."
  375.               | _ -> pp f " ;.."
  376.         in
  377.         pp f "@[<hov2><@ %a%a@ > @]"
  378.           (list core_field_type ~sep:";") l
  379.           field_var o (* Cf #7200 *)
  380.     | Ptyp_class (li, l) ->   (*FIXME*)
  381.         pp f "@[<hov2>%a#%a@]"
  382.           (list (core_type ctxt) ~sep:"," ~first:"(" ~last:")") l
  383.           longident_loc li
  384.     | Ptyp_package (lid, cstrs) ->
  385.         let aux f (s, ct) =
  386.           pp f "type %a@ =@ %a" longident_loc s (core_type ctxt) ct  in
  387.         (match cstrs with
  388.          |[] -> pp f "@[<hov2>(module@ %a)@]" longident_loc lid
  389.          |_ ->
  390.              pp f "@[<hov2>(module@ %a@ with@ %a)@]" longident_loc lid
  391.                (list aux  ~sep:"@ and@ ")  cstrs)
  392.     | Ptyp_extension e -> extension ctxt f e
  393.     | _ -> paren true (core_type ctxt) f x

  395. (********************pattern********************)
  396. (* be cautious when use [pattern], [pattern1] is preferred *)
  397. and pattern ctxt f x =
  398.   if x.ppat_attributes <> [] then begin
  399.     pp f "((%a)%a)" (pattern ctxt) {x with ppat_attributes=[]}
  400.       (attributes ctxt) x.ppat_attributes
  401.   end
  402.   else match x.ppat_desc with
  403.     | Ppat_alias (p, s) ->
  404.         pp f "@[<2>%a@;as@;%a@]" (pattern ctxt) p protect_ident s.txt
  405.     | _ -> pattern_or ctxt f x

  407. and pattern_or ctxt f x =
  408.   let rec left_associative x acc = match x with
  409.     | {ppat_desc=Ppat_or (p1,p2); ppat_attributes = []} ->
  410.         left_associative p1 (p2 :: acc)
  411.     | x -> x :: acc
  412.   in
  413.   match left_associative x [] with
  414.   | [] -> assert false
  415.   | [x] -> pattern1 ctxt f x
  416.   | orpats ->
  417.       pp f "@[<hov0>%a@]" (list ~sep:"@ | " (pattern1 ctxt)) orpats

  419. and pattern1 ctxt (f:Format.formatter) (x:pattern) : unit =
  420.   let rec pattern_list_helper f = function
  421.     | {ppat_desc =
  422.          Ppat_construct
  423.            ({ txt = Lident("::") ;_},
  424.             Some ([], {ppat_desc = Ppat_tuple([pat1; pat2]);_}));
  425.        ppat_attributes = []}

  427.       ->
  428.         pp f "%a::%a" (simple_pattern ctxt) pat1 pattern_list_helper pat2 (*RA*)
  429.     | p -> pattern1 ctxt f p
  430.   in
  431.   if x.ppat_attributes <> [] then pattern ctxt f x
  432.   else match x.ppat_desc with
  433.     | Ppat_variant (l, Some p) ->
  434.         pp f "@[<2>`%s@;%a@]" l (simple_pattern ctxt) p
  435.     | Ppat_construct (({txt=Lident("()"|"[]");_}), _) ->
  436.         simple_pattern ctxt f x
  437.     | Ppat_construct (({txt;_} as li), po) ->
  438.         (* FIXME The third field always false *)
  439.         if txt = Lident "::" then
  440.           pp f "%a" pattern_list_helper x
  441.         else
  442.           (match po with
  443.            | Some ([], x) ->
  444.                pp f "%a@;%a"  longident_loc li (simple_pattern ctxt) x
  445.            | Some (vl, x) ->
  446.                pp f "%a@ (type %a)@;%a" longident_loc li
  447.                  (list ~sep:"@ " string_loc) vl
  448.                  (simple_pattern ctxt) x
  449.            | None -> pp f "%a" longident_loc li)
  450.     | _ -> simple_pattern ctxt f x

  452. and simple_pattern ctxt (f:Format.formatter) (x:pattern) : unit =
  453.   if x.ppat_attributes <> [] then pattern ctxt f x
  454.   else match x.ppat_desc with
  455.     | Ppat_construct (({txt=Lident ("()"|"[]" as x);_}), None) ->
  456.         pp f  "%s" x
  457.     | Ppat_any -> pp f "_";
  458.     | Ppat_var ({txt = txt;_}) -> protect_ident f txt
  459.     | Ppat_array l ->
  460.         pp f "@[<2>[|%a|]@]"  (list (pattern1 ctxt) ~sep:";") l
  461.     | Ppat_unpack { txt = None } ->
  462.         pp f "(module@ _)@ "
  463.     | Ppat_unpack { txt = Some s } ->
  464.         pp f "(module@ %s)@ " s
  465.     | Ppat_type li ->
  466.         pp f "#%a" longident_loc li
  467.     | Ppat_record (l, closed) ->
  468.         let longident_x_pattern f (li, p) =
  469.           match (li,p) with
  470.           | ({txt=Lident s;_ },
  471.              {ppat_desc=Ppat_var {txt;_};
  472.               ppat_attributes=[]; _})
  473.             when s = txt ->
  474.               pp f "@[<2>%a@]"  longident_loc li
  475.           | _ ->
  476.               pp f "@[<2>%a@;=@;%a@]" longident_loc li (pattern1 ctxt) p
  477.         in
  478.         begin match closed with
  479.         | Closed ->
  480.             pp f "@[<2>{@;%a@;}@]" (list longident_x_pattern ~sep:";@;") l
  481.         | _ ->
  482.             pp f "@[<2>{@;%a;_}@]" (list longident_x_pattern ~sep:";@;") l
  483.         end
  484.     | Ppat_tuple l ->
  485.         pp f "@[<1>(%a)@]" (list  ~sep:",@;" (pattern1 ctxt))  l (* level1*)
  486.     | Ppat_constant (c) -> pp f "%a" constant c
  487.     | Ppat_interval (c1, c2) -> pp f "%a..%a" constant c1 constant c2
  488.     | Ppat_variant (l,None) ->  pp f "`%s" l
  489.     | Ppat_constraint (p, ct) ->
  490.         pp f "@[<2>(%a@;:@;%a)@]" (pattern1 ctxt) p (core_type ctxt) ct
  491.     | Ppat_lazy p ->
  492.         pp f "@[<2>(lazy@;%a)@]" (simple_pattern ctxt) p
  493.     | Ppat_exception p ->
  494.         pp f "@[<2>exception@;%a@]" (pattern1 ctxt) p
  495.     | Ppat_extension e -> extension ctxt f e
  496.     | Ppat_open (lid, p) ->
  497.         let with_paren =
  498.         match p.ppat_desc with
  499.         | Ppat_array _ | Ppat_record _
  500.         | Ppat_construct (({txt=Lident ("()"|"[]");_}), None) -> false
  501.         | _ -> true in
  502.         pp f "@[<2>%a.%a @]" longident_loc lid
  503.           (paren with_paren @@ pattern1 ctxt) p
  504.     | _ -> paren true (pattern ctxt) f x

  506. and label_exp ctxt f (l,opt,p) =
  507.   match l with
  508.   | Nolabel ->
  509.       (* single case pattern parens needed here *)
  510.       pp f "%a@ " (simple_pattern ctxt) p
  511.   | Optional rest ->
  512.       begin match p with
  513.       | {ppat_desc = Ppat_var {txt;_}; ppat_attributes = []}
  514.         when txt = rest ->
  515.           (match opt with
  516.            | Some o -> pp f "?(%s=@;%a)@;" rest  (expression ctxt) o
  517.            | None -> pp f "?%s@ " rest)
  518.       | _ ->
  519.           (match opt with
  520.            | Some o ->
  521.                pp f "?%s:(%a=@;%a)@;"
  522.                  rest (pattern1 ctxt) p (expression ctxt) o
  523.            | None -> pp f "?%s:%a@;" rest (simple_pattern ctxt) p)
  524.       end
  525.   | Labelled l -> match p with
  526.     | {ppat_desc  = Ppat_var {txt;_}; ppat_attributes = []}
  527.       when txt = l ->
  528.         pp f "~%s@;" l
  529.     | _ ->  pp f "~%s:%a@;" l (simple_pattern ctxt) p

  531. and sugar_expr ctxt f e =
  532.   if e.pexp_attributes <> [] then false
  533.   else match e.pexp_desc with
  534.   | Pexp_apply ({ pexp_desc = Pexp_ident {txt = id; _};
  535.                   pexp_attributes=[]; _}, args)
  536.     when List.for_all (fun (lab, _) -> lab = Nolabel) args -> begin
  537.       let print_indexop a path_prefix assign left sep right print_index indices
  538.           rem_args =
  539.         let print_path ppf = function
  540.           | None -> ()
  541.           | Some m -> pp ppf ".%a" longident m in
  542.         match assign, rem_args with
  543.             | false, [] ->
  544.               pp f "@[%a%a%s%a%s@]"
  545.                 (simple_expr ctxt) a print_path path_prefix
  546.                 left (list ~sep print_index) indices right; true
  547.             | true, [v] ->
  548.               pp f "@[%a%a%s%a%s@ <-@;<1 2>%a@]"
  549.                 (simple_expr ctxt) a print_path path_prefix
  550.                 left (list ~sep print_index) indices right
  551.                 (simple_expr ctxt) v; true
  552.             | _ -> false in
  553.       match id, List.map snd args with
  554.       | Lident "!", [e] ->
  555.         pp f "@[<hov>!%a@]" (simple_expr ctxt) e; true
  556.       | Ldot (path, ("get"|"set" as func)), a :: other_args -> begin
  557.           let assign = func = "set" in
  558.           let print = print_indexop a None assign in
  559.           match path, other_args with
  560.           | Lident "Array", i :: rest ->
  561.             print ".(" "" ")" (expression ctxt) [i] rest
  562.           | Lident "String", i :: rest ->
  563.             print ".[" "" "]" (expression ctxt) [i] rest
  564.           | Ldot (Lident "Bigarray", "Array1"), i1 :: rest ->
  565.             print ".{" "," "}" (simple_expr ctxt) [i1] rest
  566.           | Ldot (Lident "Bigarray", "Array2"), i1 :: i2 :: rest ->
  567.             print ".{" "," "}" (simple_expr ctxt) [i1; i2] rest
  568.           | Ldot (Lident "Bigarray", "Array3"), i1 :: i2 :: i3 :: rest ->
  569.             print ".{" "," "}" (simple_expr ctxt) [i1; i2; i3] rest
  570.           | Ldot (Lident "Bigarray", "Genarray"),
  571.             {pexp_desc = Pexp_array indexes; pexp_attributes = []} :: rest ->
  572.               print ".{" "," "}" (simple_expr ctxt) indexes rest
  573.           | _ -> false
  574.         end
  575.       | (Lident s | Ldot(_,s)) , a :: i :: rest
  576.         when first_is '.' s ->
  577.           (* extract operator:
  578.              assignment operators end with [right_bracket ^ "<-"],
  579.              access operators end with [right_bracket] directly
  580.           *)
  581.           let multi_indices = String.contains s ';' in
  582.           let i =
  583.               match i.pexp_desc with
  584.                 | Pexp_array l when multi_indices -> l
  585.                 | _ -> [ i ] in
  586.           let assign = last_is '-' s in
  587.           let kind =
  588.             (* extract the right end bracket *)
  589.             let n = String.length s in
  590.             if assign then s.[n - 3] else s.[n - 1] in
  591. ‌          let left, right = match kind with
  592.             | ')' -> '(', ")"
  593.             | ']' -> '[', "]"
  594.             | '}' -> '{', "}"
  595.             | _ -> assert false in
  596.           let path_prefix = match id with
  597.             | Ldot(m,_) -> Some m
  598.             | _ -> None in
  599.           let left = String.sub s 0 (1+String.index s left) in
  600.           print_indexop a path_prefix assign left ";" right
  601.             (if multi_indices then expression ctxt else simple_expr ctxt)
  602.             i rest
  603.       | _ -> false
  604.     end
  605.   | _ -> false

  607. ‌and expression ctxt f x =
  608.   if x.pexp_attributes <> [] then
  609.     pp f "((%a)@,%a)" (expression ctxt) {x with pexp_attributes=[]}
  610.       (attributes ctxt) x.pexp_attributes
  611.   else match x.pexp_desc with
  612.     | Pexp_function _ | Pexp_fun _ | Pexp_match _ | Pexp_try _ | Pexp_sequence _
  613.     | Pexp_newtype _
  614.       when ctxt.pipe || ctxt.semi ->
  615.         paren true (expression reset_ctxt) f x
  616.     | Pexp_ifthenelse _ | Pexp_sequence _ when ctxt.ifthenelse ->
  617.         paren true (expression reset_ctxt) f x
  618.     | Pexp_let _ | Pexp_letmodule _ | Pexp_open _
  619.       | Pexp_letexception _ | Pexp_letop _
  620.         when ctxt.semi ->
  621.         paren true (expression reset_ctxt) f x
  622.     | Pexp_fun (l, e0, p, e) ->
  623.         pp f "@[<2>fun@;%a->@;%a@]"
  624.           (label_exp ctxt) (l, e0, p)
  625.           (expression ctxt) e
  626.     | Pexp_newtype (lid, e) ->
  627.         pp f "@[<2>fun@;(type@;%s)@;->@;%a@]" lid.txt
  628.           (expression ctxt) e
  629.     | Pexp_function l ->
  630.         pp f "@[<hv>function%a@]" (case_list ctxt) l
  631.     | Pexp_match (e, l) ->
  632.         pp f "@[<hv0>@[<hv0>@[<2>match %a@]@ with@]%a@]"
  633.           (expression reset_ctxt) e (case_list ctxt) l

  635.     | Pexp_try (e, l) ->
  636.         pp f "@[<0>@[<hv2>try@ %a@]@ @[<0>with%a@]@]"
  637.              (* "try@;@[<2>%a@]@\nwith@\n%a"*)
  638.           (expression reset_ctxt) e  (case_list ctxt) l
  639.     | Pexp_let (rf, l, e) ->
  640.         (* pp f "@[<2>let %a%a in@;<1 -2>%a@]"
  641.            (*no indentation here, a new line*) *)
  642.         (*   rec_flag rf *)
  643.         pp f "@[<2>%a in@;<1 -2>%a@]"
  644.           (bindings reset_ctxt) (rf,l)
  645.           (expression ctxt) e
  646.     | Pexp_apply (e, l) ->
  647.         begin if not (sugar_expr ctxt f x) then
  648.             match view_fixity_of_exp e with
  649.             | `Infix s ->
  650.                 begin match l with
  651.                 | [ (Nolabel, _) as arg1; (Nolabel, _) as arg2 ] ->
  652.                     (* FIXME associativity label_x_expression_param *)
  653.                     pp f "@[<2>%a@;%s@;%a@]"
  654.                       (label_x_expression_param reset_ctxt) arg1 s
  655.                       (label_x_expression_param ctxt) arg2
  656.                 | _ ->
  657.                     pp f "@[<2>%a %a@]"
  658.                       (simple_expr ctxt) e
  659.                       (list (label_x_expression_param ctxt)) l
  660.                 end
  661.             | `Prefix s ->
  662. ‌                let s =
  663.                   if List.mem s ["~+";"~-";"~+.";"~-."] &&
  664.                    (match l with
  665.                     (* See #7200: avoid turning (~- 1) into (- 1) which is
  666.                        parsed as an int literal *)
  667.                     |[(_,{pexp_desc=Pexp_constant _})] -> false
  668.                     | _ -> true)
  669.                   then String.sub s 1 (String.length s -1)
  670.                   else s in
  671.                 begin match l with
  672.                 | [(Nolabel, x)] ->
  673.                   pp f "@[<2>%s@;%a@]" s (simple_expr ctxt) x
  674.                 | _   ->
  675.                   pp f "@[<2>%a %a@]" (simple_expr ctxt) e
  676.                     (list (label_x_expression_param ctxt)) l
  677.                 end
  678.             | _ ->
  679.                 pp f "@[<hov2>%a@]" begin fun f (e,l) ->
  680.                   pp f "%a@ %a" (expression2 ctxt) e
  681.                     (list (label_x_expression_param reset_ctxt))  l
  682.                     (* reset here only because [function,match,try,sequence]
  683.                        are lower priority *)
  684.                 end (e,l)
  685.         end

  687.     | Pexp_construct (li, Some eo)
  688.       when not (is_simple_construct (view_expr x))-> (* Not efficient FIXME*)
  689.         (match view_expr x with
  690.          | `cons ls -> list (simple_expr ctxt) f ls ~sep:"@;::@;"
  691.          | `normal ->
  692.              pp f "@[<2>%a@;%a@]" longident_loc li
  693.                (simple_expr ctxt) eo
  694.          | _ -> assert false)
  695.     | Pexp_setfield (e1, li, e2) ->
  696.         pp f "@[<2>%a.%a@ <-@ %a@]"
  697.           (simple_expr ctxt) e1 longident_loc li (simple_expr ctxt) e2
  698.     | Pexp_ifthenelse (e1, e2, eo) ->
  699.         (* @;@[<2>else@ %a@]@] *)
  700. ‌        let fmt:(_,_,_)format ="@[<hv0>@[<2>if@ %a@]@;@[<2>then@ %a@]%a@]" in
  701. ‌        let expression_under_ifthenelse = expression (under_ifthenelse ctxt) in
  702.         pp f fmt expression_under_ifthenelse e1 expression_under_ifthenelse e2
  703.           (fun f eo -> match eo with
  704.              | Some x ->
  705.                  pp f "@;@[<2>else@;%a@]" (expression (under_semi ctxt)) x
  706.              | None -> () (* pp f "()" *)) eo
  707.     | Pexp_sequence _ ->
  708. ‌        let rec sequence_helper acc = function
  709.           | {pexp_desc=Pexp_sequence(e1,e2); pexp_attributes = []} ->
  710.               sequence_helper (e1::acc) e2
  711.           | v -> List.rev (v::acc) in
  712. ‌        let lst = sequence_helper [] x in
  713.         pp f "@[<hv>%a@]"
  714.           (list (expression (under_semi ctxt)) ~sep:";@;") lst
  715.     | Pexp_new (li) ->
  716.         pp f "@[<hov2>new@ %a@]" longident_loc li;
  717.     | Pexp_setinstvar (s, e) ->
  718.         pp f "@[<hov2>%s@ <-@ %a@]" s.txt (expression ctxt) e
  719.     | Pexp_override l -> (* FIXME *)
  720. ‌        let string_x_expression f (s, e) =
  721.           pp f "@[<hov2>%s@ =@ %a@]" s.txt (expression ctxt) e in
  722.         pp f "@[<hov2>{<%a>}@]"
  723.           (list string_x_expression  ~sep:";"  )  l;
  724.     | Pexp_letmodule (s, me, e) ->
  725.         pp f "@[<hov2>let@ module@ %s@ =@ %a@ in@ %a@]"
  726. ‌          (Option.value s.txt ~default:"_")
  727.           (module_expr reset_ctxt) me (expression ctxt) e
  728.     | Pexp_letexception (cd, e) ->
  729.         pp f "@[<hov2>let@ exception@ %a@ in@ %a@]"
  730.           (extension_constructor ctxt) cd
  731.           (expression ctxt) e
  732.     | Pexp_assert e ->
  733.         pp f "@[<hov2>assert@ %a@]" (simple_expr ctxt) e
  734.     | Pexp_lazy (e) ->
  735.         pp f "@[<hov2>lazy@ %a@]" (simple_expr ctxt) e
  736.     (* Pexp_poly: impossible but we should print it anyway, rather than
  737.        assert false *)
  738.     | Pexp_poly (e, None) ->
  739.         pp f "@[<hov2>!poly!@ %a@]" (simple_expr ctxt) e
  740.     | Pexp_poly (e, Some ct) ->
  741.         pp f "@[<hov2>(!poly!@ %a@ : %a)@]"
  742.           (simple_expr ctxt) e (core_type ctxt) ct
  743.     | Pexp_open (o, e) ->
  744.         pp f "@[<2>let open%s %a in@;%a@]"
  745.           (override o.popen_override) (module_expr ctxt) o.popen_expr
  746.           (expression ctxt) e
  747.     | Pexp_variant (l,Some eo) ->
  748.         pp f "@[<2>`%s@;%a@]" l (simple_expr ctxt) eo
  749.     | Pexp_letop {let_; ands; body} ->
  750.         pp f "@[<2>@[<v>%a@,%a@] in@;<1 -2>%a@]"
  751.           (binding_op ctxt) let_
  752.           (list ~sep:"@," (binding_op ctxt)) ands
  753.           (expression ctxt) body
  754.     | Pexp_extension e -> extension ctxt f e
  755.     | Pexp_unreachable -> pp f "."
  756.     | _ -> expression1 ctxt f x

  758. and expression1 ctxt f x =
  759.   if x.pexp_attributes <> [] then expression ctxt f x
  760.   else match x.pexp_desc with
  761.     | Pexp_object cs -> pp f "%a" (class_structure ctxt) cs
  762.     | _ -> expression2 ctxt f x
  763. (* used in [Pexp_apply] *)

  765. and expression2 ctxt f x =
  766.   if x.pexp_attributes <> [] then expression ctxt f x
  767.   else match x.pexp_desc with
  768.     | Pexp_field (e, li) ->
  769.         pp f "@[<hov2>%a.%a@]" (simple_expr ctxt) e longident_loc li
  770.     | Pexp_send (e, s) -> pp f "@[<hov2>%a#%s@]" (simple_expr ctxt) e s.txt

  772.     | _ -> simple_expr ctxt f x

  774. and simple_expr ctxt f x =
  775.   if x.pexp_attributes <> [] then expression ctxt f x
  776.   else match x.pexp_desc with
  777.     | Pexp_construct _  when is_simple_construct (view_expr x) ->
  778.         (match view_expr x with
  779.          | `nil -> pp f "[]"
  780.          | `tuple -> pp f "()"
  781.          | `list xs ->
  782.              pp f "@[<hv0>[%a]@]"
  783.                (list (expression (under_semi ctxt)) ~sep:";@;") xs
  784.          | `simple x -> longident f x
  785.          | _ -> assert false)
  786.     | Pexp_ident li ->
  787.         longident_loc f li
  788.     (* (match view_fixity_of_exp x with *)
  789.     (* |`Normal -> longident_loc f li *)
  790.     (* | `Prefix _ | `Infix _ -> pp f "( %a )" longident_loc li) *)
  791.     | Pexp_constant c -> constant f c;
  792.     | Pexp_pack me ->
  793.         pp f "(module@;%a)" (module_expr ctxt) me
  794.     | Pexp_tuple l ->
  795.         pp f "@[<hov2>(%a)@]" (list (simple_expr ctxt) ~sep:",@;") l
  796.     | Pexp_constraint (e, ct) ->
  797.         pp f "(%a : %a)" (expression ctxt) e (core_type ctxt) ct
  798.     | Pexp_coerce (e, cto1, ct) ->
  799.         pp f "(%a%a :> %a)" (expression ctxt) e
  800.           (option (core_type ctxt) ~first:" : " ~last:" ") cto1 (* no sep hint*)
  801.           (core_type ctxt) ct
  802.     | Pexp_variant (l, None) -> pp f "`%s" l
  803.     | Pexp_record (l, eo) ->
  804.         let longident_x_expression f ( li, e) =
  805.           match e with
  806.           |  {pexp_desc=Pexp_ident {txt;_};
  807.               pexp_attributes=[]; _} when li.txt = txt ->
  808.               pp f "@[<hov2>%a@]" longident_loc li
  809.           | _ ->
  810.               pp f "@[<hov2>%a@;=@;%a@]" longident_loc li (simple_expr ctxt) e
  811.         in
  812.         pp f "@[<hv0>@[<hv2>{@;%a%a@]@;}@]"(* "@[<hov2>{%a%a}@]" *)
  813.           (option ~last:" with@;" (simple_expr ctxt)) eo
  814.           (list longident_x_expression ~sep:";@;") l
  815.     | Pexp_array (l) ->
  816.         pp f "@[<0>@[<2>[|%a|]@]@]"
  817.           (list (simple_expr (under_semi ctxt)) ~sep:";") l
  818.     | Pexp_while (e1, e2) ->
  819.         let fmt : (_,_,_) format = "@[<2>while@;%a@;do@;%a@;done@]" in
  820.         pp f fmt (expression ctxt) e1 (expression ctxt) e2
  821.     | Pexp_for (s, e1, e2, df, e3) ->
  822.         let fmt:(_,_,_)format =
  823.           "@[<hv0>@[<hv2>@[<2>for %a =@;%a@;%a%a@;do@]@;%a@]@;done@]" in
  824.         let expression = expression ctxt in
  825.         pp f fmt (pattern ctxt) s expression e1 direction_flag
  826.           df expression e2 expression e3
  827.     | _ ->  paren true (expression ctxt) f x

  829. and attributes ctxt f l =
  830.   List.iter (attribute ctxt f) l

  832. and item_attributes ctxt f l =
  833.   List.iter (item_attribute ctxt f) l

  835. and attribute ctxt f a =
  836.   pp f "@[<2>[@@%s@ %a]@]" a.attr_name.txt (payload ctxt) a.attr_payload

  838. and item_attribute ctxt f a =
  839.   pp f "@[<2>[@@@@%s@ %a]@]" a.attr_name.txt (payload ctxt) a.attr_payload

  841. and floating_attribute ctxt f a =
  842.   pp f "@[<2>[@@@@@@%s@ %a]@]" a.attr_name.txt (payload ctxt) a.attr_payload

  844. and value_description ctxt f x =
  845.   (* note: value_description has an attribute field,
  846.            but they're already printed by the callers this method *)
  847.   pp f "@[<hov2>%a%a@]" (core_type ctxt) x.pval_type
  848.     (fun f x ->
  849.        if x.pval_prim <> []
  850.        then pp f "@ =@ %a" (list constant_string) x.pval_prim
  851.     ) x

  853. and extension ctxt f (s, e) =
  854.   pp f "@[<2>[%%%s@ %a]@]" s.txt (payload ctxt) e

  856. and item_extension ctxt f (s, e) =
  857.   pp f "@[<2>[%%%%%s@ %a]@]" s.txt (payload ctxt) e

  859. and exception_declaration ctxt f x =
  860.   pp f "@[<hov2>exception@ %a@]%a"
  861.     (extension_constructor ctxt) x.ptyexn_constructor
  862.     (item_attributes ctxt) x.ptyexn_attributes

  864. and class_type_field ctxt f x =
  865.   match x.pctf_desc with
  866.   | Pctf_inherit (ct) ->
  867.       pp f "@[<2>inherit@ %a@]%a" (class_type ctxt) ct
  868.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pctf_attributes
  869.   | Pctf_val (s, mf, vf, ct) ->
  870.       pp f "@[<2>val @ %a%a%s@ :@ %a@]%a"
  871.         mutable_flag mf virtual_flag vf s.txt (core_type ctxt) ct
  872.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pctf_attributes
  873.   | Pctf_method (s, pf, vf, ct) ->
  874.       pp f "@[<2>method %a %a%s :@;%a@]%a"
  875.         private_flag pf virtual_flag vf s.txt (core_type ctxt) ct
  876.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pctf_attributes
  877.   | Pctf_constraint (ct1, ct2) ->
  878.       pp f "@[<2>constraint@ %a@ =@ %a@]%a"
  879.         (core_type ctxt) ct1 (core_type ctxt) ct2
  880.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pctf_attributes
  881.   | Pctf_attribute a -> floating_attribute ctxt f a
  882.   | Pctf_extension e ->
  883.       item_extension ctxt f e;
  884.       item_attributes ctxt f x.pctf_attributes

  886. and class_signature ctxt f { pcsig_self = ct; pcsig_fields = l ;_} =
  887.   pp f "@[<hv0>@[<hv2>object@[<1>%a@]@ %a@]@ end@]"
  888.     (fun f -> function
  889.          {ptyp_desc=Ptyp_any; ptyp_attributes=[]; _} -> ()
  890.        | ct -> pp f " (%a)" (core_type ctxt) ct) ct
  891.     (list (class_type_field ctxt) ~sep:"@;") l

  893. (* call [class_signature] called by [class_signature] *)
  894. and class_type ctxt f x =
  895.   match x.pcty_desc with
  896.   | Pcty_signature cs ->
  897.       class_signature ctxt f cs;
  898.       attributes ctxt f x.pcty_attributes
  899.   | Pcty_constr (li, l) ->
  900.       pp f "%a%a%a"
  901.         (fun f l -> match l with
  902.            | [] -> ()
  903.            | _  -> pp f "[%a]@ " (list (core_type ctxt) ~sep:"," ) l) l
  904.         longident_loc li
  905.         (attributes ctxt) x.pcty_attributes
  906.   | Pcty_arrow (l, co, cl) ->
  907.       pp f "@[<2>%a@;->@;%a@]" (* FIXME remove parens later *)
  908.         (type_with_label ctxt) (l,co)
  909.         (class_type ctxt) cl
  910.   | Pcty_extension e ->
  911.       extension ctxt f e;
  912.       attributes ctxt f x.pcty_attributes
  913.   | Pcty_open (o, e) ->
  914.       pp f "@[<2>let open%s %a in@;%a@]"
  915.         (override o.popen_override) longident_loc o.popen_expr
  916.         (class_type ctxt) e

  918. (* [class type a = object end] *)
  919. and class_type_declaration_list ctxt f l =
  920.   let class_type_declaration kwd f x =
  921.     let { pci_params=ls; pci_name={ txt; _ }; _ } = x in
  922.     pp f "@[<2>%s %a%a%s@ =@ %a@]%a" kwd
  923.       virtual_flag x.pci_virt
  924.       (class_params_def ctxt) ls txt
  925.       (class_type ctxt) x.pci_expr
  926.       (item_attributes ctxt) x.pci_attributes
  927.   in
  928.   match l with
  929.   | [] -> ()
  930.   | [x] -> class_type_declaration "class type" f x
  931.   | x :: xs ->
  932.       pp f "@[<v>%a@,%a@]"
  933.         (class_type_declaration "class type") x
  934.         (list ~sep:"@," (class_type_declaration "and")) xs

  936. and class_field ctxt f x =
  937.   match x.pcf_desc with
  938.   | Pcf_inherit (ovf, ce, so) ->
  939.       pp f "@[<2>inherit@ %s@ %a%a@]%a" (override ovf)
  940.         (class_expr ctxt) ce
  941.         (fun f so -> match so with
  942.            | None -> ();
  943.            | Some (s) -> pp f "@ as %s" s.txt ) so
  944.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pcf_attributes
  945.   | Pcf_val (s, mf, Cfk_concrete (ovf, e)) ->
  946.       pp f "@[<2>val%s %a%s =@;%a@]%a" (override ovf)
  947.         mutable_flag mf s.txt
  948.         (expression ctxt) e
  949.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pcf_attributes
  950.   | Pcf_method (s, pf, Cfk_virtual ct) ->
  951.       pp f "@[<2>method virtual %a %s :@;%a@]%a"
  952.         private_flag pf s.txt
  953.         (core_type ctxt) ct
  954.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pcf_attributes
  955.   | Pcf_val (s, mf, Cfk_virtual ct) ->
  956.       pp f "@[<2>val virtual %a%s :@ %a@]%a"
  957.         mutable_flag mf s.txt
  958.         (core_type ctxt) ct
  959.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pcf_attributes
  960.   | Pcf_method (s, pf, Cfk_concrete (ovf, e)) ->
  961.       let bind e =
  962.         binding ctxt f
  963.           {pvb_pat=
  964.              {ppat_desc=Ppat_var s;
  965.               ppat_loc=Location.none;
  966.               ppat_loc_stack=[];
  967.               ppat_attributes=[]};
  968.            pvb_expr=e;
  969.            pvb_constraint=None;
  970.            pvb_attributes=[];
  971.            pvb_loc=Location.none;
  972.           }
  973.       in
  974.       pp f "@[<2>method%s %a%a@]%a"
  975.         (override ovf)
  976.         private_flag pf
  977.         (fun f -> function
  978.            | {pexp_desc=Pexp_poly (e, Some ct); pexp_attributes=[]; _} ->
  979.                pp f "%s :@;%a=@;%a"
  980.                  s.txt (core_type ctxt) ct (expression ctxt) e
  981.            | {pexp_desc=Pexp_poly (e, None); pexp_attributes=[]; _} ->
  982.                bind e
  983.            | _ -> bind e) e
  984.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pcf_attributes
  985.   | Pcf_constraint (ct1, ct2) ->
  986.       pp f "@[<2>constraint %a =@;%a@]%a"
  987.         (core_type ctxt) ct1
  988.         (core_type ctxt) ct2
  989.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pcf_attributes
  990.   | Pcf_initializer (e) ->
  991.       pp f "@[<2>initializer@ %a@]%a"
  992.         (expression ctxt) e
  993.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pcf_attributes
  994.   | Pcf_attribute a -> floating_attribute ctxt f a
  995.   | Pcf_extension e ->
  996.       item_extension ctxt f e;
  997.       item_attributes ctxt f x.pcf_attributes

  999. and class_structure ctxt f { pcstr_self = p; pcstr_fields =  l } =
  1000.   pp f "@[<hv0>@[<hv2>object%a@;%a@]@;end@]"
  1001.     (fun f p -> match p.ppat_desc with
  1002.        | Ppat_any -> ()
  1003.        | Ppat_constraint _ -> pp f " %a" (pattern ctxt) p
  1004.        | _ -> pp f " (%a)" (pattern ctxt) p) p
  1005.     (list (class_field ctxt)) l

  1007. and class_expr ctxt f x =
  1008.   if x.pcl_attributes <> [] then begin
  1009.     pp f "((%a)%a)" (class_expr ctxt) {x with pcl_attributes=[]}
  1010.       (attributes ctxt) x.pcl_attributes
  1011.   end else
  1012.     match x.pcl_desc with
  1013.     | Pcl_structure (cs) -> class_structure ctxt f cs
  1014.     | Pcl_fun (l, eo, p, e) ->
  1015.         pp f "fun@ %a@ ->@ %a"
  1016.           (label_exp ctxt) (l,eo,p)
  1017.           (class_expr ctxt) e
  1018.     | Pcl_let (rf, l, ce) ->
  1019.         pp f "%a@ in@ %a"
  1020.           (bindings ctxt) (rf,l)
  1021.           (class_expr ctxt) ce
  1022.     | Pcl_apply (ce, l) ->
  1023.         pp f "((%a)@ %a)" (* Cf: #7200 *)
  1024.           (class_expr ctxt) ce
  1025.           (list (label_x_expression_param ctxt)) l
  1026.     | Pcl_constr (li, l) ->
  1027.         pp f "%a%a"
  1028.           (fun f l-> if l <>[] then
  1029.               pp f "[%a]@ "
  1030.                 (list (core_type ctxt) ~sep:",") l) l
  1031.           longident_loc li
  1032.     | Pcl_constraint (ce, ct) ->
  1033.         pp f "(%a@ :@ %a)"
  1034.           (class_expr ctxt) ce
  1035.           (class_type ctxt) ct
  1036.     | Pcl_extension e -> extension ctxt f e
  1037.     | Pcl_open (o, e) ->
  1038.         pp f "@[<2>let open%s %a in@;%a@]"
  1039.           (override o.popen_override) longident_loc o.popen_expr
  1040.           (class_expr ctxt) e

  1042. and module_type ctxt f x =
  1043.   if x.pmty_attributes <> [] then begin
  1044.     pp f "((%a)%a)" (module_type ctxt) {x with pmty_attributes=[]}
  1045.       (attributes ctxt) x.pmty_attributes
  1046.   end else
  1047.     match x.pmty_desc with
  1048.     | Pmty_functor (Unit, mt2) ->
  1049.         pp f "@[<hov2>() ->@ %a@]" (module_type ctxt) mt2
  1050.     | Pmty_functor (Named (s, mt1), mt2) ->
  1051.         begin match s.txt with
  1052.         | None ->
  1053.             pp f "@[<hov2>%a@ ->@ %a@]"
  1054.               (module_type1 ctxt) mt1 (module_type ctxt) mt2
  1055.         | Some name ->
  1056.             pp f "@[<hov2>functor@ (%s@ :@ %a)@ ->@ %a@]" name
  1057.               (module_type ctxt) mt1 (module_type ctxt) mt2
  1058.         end
  1059.     | Pmty_with (mt, []) -> module_type ctxt f mt
  1060.     | Pmty_with (mt, l) ->
  1061.         pp f "@[<hov2>%a@ with@ %a@]"
  1062.           (module_type1 ctxt) mt
  1063.           (list (with_constraint ctxt) ~sep:"@ and@ ") l
  1064.     | _ -> module_type1 ctxt f x

  1066. and with_constraint ctxt f = function
  1067.   | Pwith_type (li, ({ptype_params= ls ;_} as td)) ->
  1068.       pp f "type@ %a %a =@ %a"
  1069.         (type_params ctxt) ls
  1070.         longident_loc li (type_declaration ctxt) td
  1071.   | Pwith_module (li, li2) ->
  1072.       pp f "module %a =@ %a" longident_loc li longident_loc li2;
  1073.   | Pwith_modtype (li, mty) ->
  1074.       pp f "module type %a =@ %a" longident_loc li (module_type ctxt) mty;
  1075.   | Pwith_typesubst (li, ({ptype_params=ls;_} as td)) ->
  1076.       pp f "type@ %a %a :=@ %a"
  1077.         (type_params ctxt) ls
  1078.         longident_loc li
  1079.         (type_declaration ctxt) td
  1080.   | Pwith_modsubst (li, li2) ->
  1081.       pp f "module %a :=@ %a" longident_loc li longident_loc li2
  1082.   | Pwith_modtypesubst (li, mty) ->
  1083.       pp f "module type %a :=@ %a" longident_loc li (module_type ctxt) mty;


  1086. and module_type1 ctxt f x =
  1087.   if x.pmty_attributes <> [] then module_type ctxt f x
  1088.   else match x.pmty_desc with
  1089.     | Pmty_ident li ->
  1090.         pp f "%a" longident_loc li;
  1091.     | Pmty_alias li ->
  1092.         pp f "(module %a)" longident_loc li;
  1093.     | Pmty_signature (s) ->
  1094.         pp f "@[<hv0>@[<hv2>sig@ %a@]@ end@]" (* "@[<hov>sig@ %a@ end@]" *)
  1095.           (list (signature_item ctxt)) s (* FIXME wrong indentation*)
  1096.     | Pmty_typeof me ->
  1097.         pp f "@[<hov2>module@ type@ of@ %a@]" (module_expr ctxt) me
  1098.     | Pmty_extension e -> extension ctxt f e
  1099.     | _ -> paren true (module_type ctxt) f x

  1101. and signature ctxt f x =  list ~sep:"@\n" (signature_item ctxt) f x

  1103. and signature_item ctxt f x : unit =
  1104.   match x.psig_desc with
  1105.   | Psig_type (rf, l) ->
  1106.       type_def_list ctxt f (rf, true, l)
  1107.   | Psig_typesubst l ->
  1108.       (* Psig_typesubst is never recursive, but we specify [Recursive] here to
  1109.          avoid printing a [nonrec] flag, which would be rejected by the parser.
  1110.       *)
  1111.       type_def_list ctxt f (Recursive, false, l)
  1112.   | Psig_value vd ->
  1113.       let intro = if vd.pval_prim = [] then "val" else "external" in
  1114.       pp f "@[<2>%s@ %a@ :@ %a@]%a" intro
  1115.         protect_ident vd.pval_name.txt
  1116.         (value_description ctxt) vd
  1117.         (item_attributes ctxt) vd.pval_attributes
  1118.   | Psig_typext te ->
  1119.       type_extension ctxt f te
  1120.   | Psig_exception ed ->
  1121.       exception_declaration ctxt f ed
  1122.   | Psig_class l ->
  1123. ‌      let class_description kwd f ({pci_params=ls;pci_name={txt;_};_} as x) =
  1124.         pp f "@[<2>%s %a%a%s@;:@;%a@]%a" kwd
  1125.           virtual_flag x.pci_virt
  1126.           (class_params_def ctxt) ls txt
  1127.           (class_type ctxt) x.pci_expr
  1128.           (item_attributes ctxt) x.pci_attributes
  1129.       in begin
  1130.         match l with
  1131.         | [] -> ()
  1132.         | [x] -> class_description "class" f x
  1133.         | x :: xs ->
  1134.             pp f "@[<v>%a@,%a@]"
  1135.               (class_description "class") x
  1136.               (list ~sep:"@," (class_description "and")) xs
  1137.       end
  1138.   | Psig_module ({pmd_type={pmty_desc=Pmty_alias alias;
  1139.                             pmty_attributes=[]; _};_} as pmd) ->
  1140.       pp f "@[<hov>module@ %s@ =@ %a@]%a"
  1141. ‌        (Option.value pmd.pmd_name.txt ~default:"_")
  1142.         longident_loc alias
  1143.         (item_attributes ctxt) pmd.pmd_attributes
  1144.   | Psig_module pmd ->
  1145.       pp f "@[<hov>module@ %s@ :@ %a@]%a"
  1146.         (Option.value pmd.pmd_name.txt ~default:"_")
  1147.         (module_type ctxt) pmd.pmd_type
  1148.         (item_attributes ctxt) pmd.pmd_attributes
  1149.   | Psig_modsubst pms ->
  1150.       pp f "@[<hov>module@ %s@ :=@ %a@]%a" pms.pms_name.txt
  1151.         longident_loc pms.pms_manifest
  1152.         (item_attributes ctxt) pms.pms_attributes
  1153.   | Psig_open od ->
  1154.       pp f "@[<hov2>open%s@ %a@]%a"
  1155.         (override od.popen_override)
  1156.         longident_loc od.popen_expr
  1157.         (item_attributes ctxt) od.popen_attributes
  1158.   | Psig_include incl ->
  1159.       pp f "@[<hov2>include@ %a@]%a"
  1160.         (module_type ctxt) incl.pincl_mod
  1161.         (item_attributes ctxt) incl.pincl_attributes
  1162.   | Psig_modtype {pmtd_name=s; pmtd_type=md; pmtd_attributes=attrs} ->
  1163.       pp f "@[<hov2>module@ type@ %s%a@]%a"
  1164.         s.txt
  1165.         (fun f md -> match md with
  1166.            | None -> ()
  1167.            | Some mt ->
  1168.                pp_print_space f () ;
  1169.                pp f "@ =@ %a" (module_type ctxt) mt
  1170.         ) md
  1171.         (item_attributes ctxt) attrs
  1172.   | Psig_modtypesubst {pmtd_name=s; pmtd_type=md; pmtd_attributes=attrs} ->
  1173. ‌      let md = match md with
  1174.         | None -> assert false (* ast invariant *)
  1175.         | Some mt -> mt in
  1176.       pp f "@[<hov2>module@ type@ %s@ :=@ %a@]%a"
  1177.         s.txt (module_type ctxt) md
  1178.         (item_attributes ctxt) attrs
  1179.   | Psig_class_type (l) -> class_type_declaration_list ctxt f l
  1180.   | Psig_recmodule decls ->
  1181. ‌      let rec  string_x_module_type_list f ?(first=true) l =
  1182.         match l with
  1183.         | [] -> () ;
  1184.         | pmd :: tl ->
  1185.             if not first then
  1186.               pp f "@ @[<hov2>and@ %s:@ %a@]%a"

  1203. and module_expr ctxt f x =

  1232. and structure ctxt f x = list ~sep:"@\n" (structure_item ctxt) f x

  1248. and binding ctxt f {pvb_pat=p; pvb_expr=x; pvb_constraint = ct; _} =

  1256.           else

  1262.   in
  1263.   match ct with
  1264.   | Some (Pvc_constraint { locally_abstract_univars = []; typ }) ->

  1271.         (core_type ctxt) typ (expression ctxt) x
  1272.   | Some (Pvc_coercion {ground=None; coercion }) ->
  1273.       pp f "%a@;:>@;%a@;=@;%a"

  1275.   | Some (Pvc_coercion {ground=Some ground; coercion }) ->
  1276.       pp f "%a@;:%a@;:>@;%a@;=@;%a"
  1277.         (simple_pattern ctxt) p
  1278.         (core_type ctxt) ground
  1279.         (core_type ctxt) coercion
  1280.         (expression ctxt) x
  1281.   | None -> begin
  1282.       match p with
  1283.       | {ppat_desc=Ppat_var _; ppat_attributes=[]} ->

  1285.       | _ ->
  1286.           pp f "%a@;=@;%a" (pattern ctxt) p (expression ctxt) x

  1289. (* [in] is not printed *)

  1326.   | Pstr_module x ->

  1347.                                | Pmty_signature (_));_} as mt));

  1351.            | _ -> pp f " =@ %a" (module_expr ctxt) me
  1352.         ) x.pmb_expr
  1353.         (item_attributes ctxt) x.pmb_attributes
  1354.   | Pstr_open od ->

  1369.   | Pstr_class l ->
